Likewiſe doeth he alſo require for thankes, laude, and prayſe, none other thing, but ye forgiue and forget your neighbours, what ſo euer they haue at any time offēded againſt you. And you ſhal not only your offenders gladly and heartily forgiue: but alſo againe, ſhewe your ſelfe againſt them thankfull. And
for the poore widowes and fatherleſſe children, according to your abilitie prouide ſomething, whereby they may be fed, clothed, and mainteined, ſo ſhal they at the laſt day be your witneſſes, that your faith was a perfect faith, ſéeing it is liuely by workes,
• ala. 6. • Pet. 1. Gala. 6. Make your election ſure, through ſuch works of loue, as Saint Peter ſaith. 2. Pet. 1.
